label: CQ_01

components.name: Quantity
components.text: This component specifies the numeric quantity or amount of an entity.

components.name: Units
components.text: This component species the units in which the quantity is expressed.

name: CQ
defPreText:
This data type carries a quantity and attendant units.

Quantity and Units required.
defPostText:
Reminder that the subcomponent separator is used when the CWE data type is a component of another data type as in RCP.2.

Example:

To request 10 records:     10^RD&Records&HL70126

label: CWE_01

components.name: Identifier
components.text: Sequence of characters (the code) that uniquely identifies the item being referenced.

components.name: Text
components.text: The descriptive or textual name of the identifier, e.g., DTaP. This is not typically used by the sending or receiving system, but rather facilitates human interpretation of the code.

components.name: Name of Coding System
components.text: Identifies the coding scheme being used in the identifier component. The combination of the identifier and coding system components will unambiguously identify the concept being messaged.

components.name: Name of Second Alternate Coding System
Second Alternate Coding System Version ID
Second Alternate Value Set Version ID

name: CWE
defPreText:
Specifies a coded element and its associated detail.

Identifier (first triplet) required, Alternate Identifier (second triplet) optional.
defPostText:
Note: If valued, the alternate identifier (CWE.4) should be the closest match for the identifier found in CWE.1, that is, they should be synonyms.

The Name of Coding System (CWE.3/CWE.6) in the message should reference the Coding System, not the Value Set.  Given the distinctions between value sets and coding system, often there is confusion as to the value to send in the message in the CWE data type. For coded data types, the coding system in the third component is drawn from table HL70396. Changes to Table 0396 occur frequently.  The most recent version of this table is available at http://www.hl7.org/special/committees/vocab/table_0396/index.cfm which contains a list of possible values.

Example:

RXA-5 (vaccine):     49281-0560-05^Pentacel^NDC

With optional alternate ID:     49281-0560-05^Pentacel^NDC^120^DTaP-Hib-IPV^CVX

label: CX_01

components.name: ID Number
components.text: The value of the identifier itself.

components.name: Assigning Authority
components.text: The assigning authority is a unique identifier of the system (or organization or agency or department) that creates the data. The first component should be used for a unique namespace. The second and third components may be used for OIDs.

components.name: Identifier Type Code
components.text: A code corresponding to the type of identifier.

name: CX
description: Extended Composite ID with Check Digit
defPreText:
This data type is used for specifying an identifier with its associated administrative detail.

ID, Assigning Authority and Identifier Type Code required.
defPostText:
The combination of the Assigning Authority (CX.4) and Identifier Type Code (CX.5) of should uniquely identify the pool of IDs from which the ID Number (CX.1) is selected.

Example:

Patient Identifier:     1234567^^^MyEHR^MR

conformanceStatements.description: The value of HD.2(Universal ID) SHALL be equal to an ISO compliant OID.
conformanceStatements.assertion: <Assertion><SimpleValue Path="2[1]" Operator="EQ" Value="an ISO compliant OID"/></Assertion>

conformanceStatements.description: The value of HD.3(Universal ID Type) SHALL be 'ISO'.

label: HD_01

comments.description: This field is used for a locally defined name

components.name: Namespace ID
components.comment: This field is used for a locally defined name
components.text: The local coded item for the entity.

components.name: Universal ID
components.text: The second component of the HD data type, the Universal ID, is a string formatted according to the scheme defined by the Universal ID Type in the third component.

components.name: Universal ID Type
components.text: The third component governs the interpretation of HD.2..

name: HD
defPreText:
The basic definition of the HD is that it identifies an entity (administrative or system or application or other) that has responsibility for managing or assigning a defined set of instance identifiers (such as patient identifiers, provider identifiers, etc.). This entity could be a particular health care application such as a registration system that assigns patient identifiers, a governmental entity such as a licensing authority that assigns professional identifiers or drivers' license numbers, or a facility where such identifiers are assigned.

Namespace ID required.

conformanceStatements.description: The value of EI.3(Universal ID) SHALL be equal to an ISO-compliant OID.
The value of EI.4(Universal ID Type) SHALL be 'ISO'.

label: EI_01

components.name: Entity Identifier
components.text:
The first component, Entity Identifier, is defined to be unique within the series of identifiers defined by the Namespace (EI.2) or the Universal ID/ID Type (EI.3 and EI.4). 

Note that EI.2, EI.3 and EI.4 combined function like the HD data type.

components.name: Namespace ID
components.text: The assigning authority is a unique identifier of the system (or organization or agency or department) that creates the data.

components.name: Universal ID
components.text: This is a universal ID associated with this entity. It must be linked to the Universal ID Type below. If populated, it shall be an OID.

name: EI
defPreText:
The entity identifier defines a given entity within a specified series of identifiers.

Namespace ID required, ability to support an OID required.
defPostText:
Example:

ORC-3 Filler Order Number:     242091^MyEHR

label: ERL_01

comments.description: This should not be populated if the error refers to the whole segment.
Should be populated ONLY when a particular component causes the error.
Should be populated ONLY when a particular sub-component causes the error.

components.name: Segment ID
components.text: Specifies the 3-character name for the segment.

components.name: Segment Sequence
components.text: Identifies the segment occurrence within the message. That is, for the first instance of the segment in the message the number shall be 1 and for the second 2.  It is not the sequence within a segment group. For example if a message had 3 order groups and each order group had 3 OBX segments, the Sequence number of the last OBX in the message would be 9.

components.name: Field Position
components.comment: This should not be populated if the error refers to the whole segment.
components.text: Identifies the number of the field within the segment. The first field is assigned a number of 1. Field position should not be specified when referring to the entire segment.

components.name: Field Repetition
components.text: Identifies the repetition number of the field. The first occurrence is counted as 1. If a Field Position is specified, but Field Repetition is not, Field Repetition should be assumed to be 1. If Field Position is not specified, Field Repetition should not be specified.

components.name: Component Number
components.comment: Should be populated ONLY when a particular component causes the error.
components.text: Identifies the number of the component within the field. The first component is assigned a number of 1. Component number should not be specified when referring to the entire field.

components.name: Sub-Component Number
components.comment: Should be populated ONLY when a particular sub-component causes the error.
components.text: Identifies the number of the sub-component within the component. The first sub-component is assigned a number of 1. Sub-component number should not be specified when referring to the entire component.

name: ERL
defPreText: This data type identifies the segment and its constituent where an error has occurred.
defPostText:
Example:

Error in the first occurrence of the fifth field of the first RXA segment:     RXA^1^5^1

label: MSG_01

components.name: Message Code
components.text: Specifies the message type code.

components.name: Trigger Event
components.text: Specifies the trigger event code.

components.name: Message Structure
components.text: Specifies the abstract message structure code.

name: MSG
defPreText:
This data type contains the message type, trigger event, and the message structure ID for the message.

All components required.
defPostText:
Example:

For the Z22 profile:     VXU^V04^VXU_V04

label: PT_01

components.name: Processing ID
components.text: A value that defines whether the message is part of a production, training, or debugging system.

name: PT
defPreText:
This data type indicates whether to process a message as defined in HL7 Application (level 7) Processing rules.

Processing ID required.

label: SAD_01

components.name: Street or Mailing Address
components.text: This component specifies the street or mailing address of a person or institution.

name: SAD
defPreText:
Appears only in the XAD data type.

Street or Mailing Address required.

conformanceStatements.description: [The value of XAD.6(Country) is 'USA'.] IFTHEN [The value of XAD.4(State or Province) SHALL be one of codes in ValueSet: USPS_State.]
conformanceStatements.assertion: <Assertion><IMPLY><PlainText Path="6[1]" Text="USA" IgnoreCase="false"/><ValueSet Path="4[1]" ValueSetID="USPS_State" BindingStrength="R" BindingLocation="1"/></IMPLY></Assertion>

label: XAD_01

comments.description: Values should be the two character USPS codes. For example, AL, AK, ME, etc

components.name: Street Address
components.text: This is the street address.

components.name: Other Designation
components.text: Second line of address. In US usage, it qualifies address. Examples: Suite 555 or Fourth Floor. This can be used for dwelling number.

components.name: City
components.text: This component specifies the city, or district or place where the addressee is located depending upon the national convention for formatting addresses for postal usage.

components.name: State or Province
components.comment: Values should be the two character USPS codes. For example, AL, AK, ME, etc
components.text: This component specifies the state or province where the addressee is located. State or province should be represented by the official postal service codes for that country.

components.name: Zip or Postal Code
components.text: This component specifies the zip or postal code where the addressee is located. Zip or postal codes should be represented by the official codes for that country. In the US, the zip code takes the form 99999[-9999], while the Canadian postal code takes the form A9A9A9, and the Australian Postcode takes the form 9999.

components.name: Country
components.text: This component specifies the country where the addressee is located. HL7 specifies that the 3-character (alphabetic) form of ISO 3166 be used for the country code.

components.name: Address Type
components.text: This component specifies the kind or type of address.

name: XAD
defPreText: This data type specifies the address of a person, place or organization plus associated information.
defPostText:
Example:

Usage for US:     1000 Hospital Lane^Ste. 123^Ann Arbor ^MI^99999^^P|

This would be formatted for postal purposes as:

1000 Hospital Lane

Ste. 123

Ann Arbor MI 99999

name: XCN
description: Extended Composite ID Number and Name for Persons
defPreText:
This data type is used where there is a need to specify the ID number and/or name of a person. 

Name or ID required.
defPostText:
Note: The ID Number component combined with the Assigning Authority (XCN.9) and ID type (XCN.13) must uniquely identify the associated person.

Example:

7824^Jackson^Lily^Suzanne^^^^^MyEHR^L^^^PRN

label: FN_01

components.name: Surname
components.text: The atomic element of the person's family name. In most Western usage, this is the person's last name.

name: FN
defPreText:
This data type allows full specification of the surname of a person. 

Surname required.

components.name: Organization Name

components.name: Assigning Authority

components.name: Organization Identifier
components.text: This component contains the sequence of characters (the code) that uniquely identifies the item being referenced by XON.1 Organization Name.

name: XON
description: Extended Composite Name and Identification Number for Organizations
defPreText:
This data type identifies an organization using a unique ID and/or name. 

Name or ID required.
defPostText: The combination of the Assigning Authority (XON.6) and the Identifier Type Code (XON.7) define a unique ID pool.

name: XTN
defPreText: This contains the extended telecommunication data. Includes phone number and email address.
defPostText:
Note: Each telecommunication use code (ie. Phone number, email address, etc) must be in its own occurrence

Example:

Home telephone number:  ^PRN^PH^^^734^5559907

Work telephone number:  ^WPN^PH^^^734^5556319

Home email address:  ^PRN^Internet^warren.jackson@isp.com

Work email address:  ^WPN^Internet^wjackson@somecompany.com

Personal mobile phone number:  ^PRS^CP^^^734^5553750

All personal telecommunication codes in a single field:  ^PRS^CP^^^734^5553750~^PRN^PH^^^734^5559907~^PRN^Internet^warren.jackson@isp.com

label: PL_01

comments.description: This represents the location that the service was provided

label: OG_01

components.name: Original Sub-Identifier
components.text: The Original Sub-Identifier component represents the original data type used in OBX-4 to enable backwards compatibility to continue use of the original format to provide OBX segment grouping.

name: OG

The data type is used to define the relationship of the observation/result segments (OBX) within a message.

label: ID_01
name: ID
description: Coded Value for HL7 Defined Tables
defPreText: This data type is used for coded values from an HL7 table.
defPostText: The value of such a field follows the formatting rules for an ST field except that it is drawn from a table of legal values.

label: IS_01
name: IS
defPreText: This data type is used for coded values from a user-defined table.
defPostText: The value of such a field follows the formatting rules for a ST field except that it is drawn from a site-defined (or user-defined) table of legal values.

label: SI_01
name: SI
defPreText: A non-negative integer in the form of a NM field. The uses of this data type are defined in the chapters defining the segments and messages in which it appears.

label: ST_01
name: ST
defPreText: String data is left justified (i.e., no leading blank space) with trailing blanks optional. Any displayable (printable) ACSII characters (hexadecimal values between 20 and 7E, inclusive, or ASCII decimal values between 32 and 126), except the defined escape characters and defined delimiter characters.
defPostText: The ST data type is normally used for short text strings. No leading blanks (space characters) are permitted. Trailing blanks are permitted. In this document, the only allowed escape sequences are those allowed in HL7 Version 2.8.2, Chapter 2, Section 2.7.5 - Special Character. These are the escape sequences for the message delimiters.

label: NM_01
name: NM
defPreText: A number represented as a series of ASCII numeric characters consisting of an optional leading sign (+ or -), the digits and an optional decimal point. In the absence of a sign, the number is assumed to be positive. If there is no decimal point the number is assumed to be an integer.
defPostText: Leading zeros, or trailing zeros after a decimal point, are not significant. For example, the following two values with different representations, "01.20" and "1.2," are identical. Except for the optional leading sign (+ or -) and the optional decimal point (.), no non-numeric ASCII characters are allowed. Thus, the value <12 should be encoded as a structured numeric (SN) (preferred) or as a string (ST) (allowed, but not preferred) data type.

label: TX_01
name: TX
defPreText: String data meant for user display. Such data would not necessarily be left justified since leading spaces may contribute greatly to the clarity of the presentation to the user. Leading spaces should be included. Trailing spaces should be removed.
defPostText: In this document, the only allowed escape sequences are those allowed in HL7 Version 2.8.2, Chapter 2, Section 2.7.4 - Special Characters. These are the escape sequences for the message delimiters (i.e., |^&~\ ).

label: EI_02

components.name: Entity Identifier
components.text: The first component, Entity Identifier, is defined to be unique within the series of identifiers defined by the Namespace (EI.2).

components.name: Namespace ID
components.text: The assigning authority is a unique identifier of the system (or organization or agency or department) that creates the data.

name: EI
defPreText:
The entity identifier defines a given entity within a specified series of identifiers.

label: SNM_01
name: SNM
defPreText:
A string whose characters are limited to "+" and/or the decimal digits 0  through 9.  As a string, leading zeros are always considered significant.

 Used in the XTN data type.
